author: saya
msg: initial changes for the txn manager. Txn manager handles, begin, commit and abort of txns. It makes use of txn log manager to log begin, abort, commit log records and order of commit records in the wal log defines a serializable order for txns. TXN management is optimized for read only txns. Read only txns do not have to insert any log record into the wal.
TxnLogManager helps txn manager to log txn marker records and also exposes an interface for txns to log changes.
Also moved log manager packages to core-api and core and replaced assert statements with illegalstate exceptions.
